<br>
The woman's hand was busy stirring something in a pot on the hook of the heart when she looked up at the sound of the door opening.<br>
<br>
Cyrene offered a bright smile and stood to full height('round 5'2&quot;) smoothing the apron that protects her skirt.  &quot;Good morning, Athelfi.&quot;<br>
<br>
Moving to the bar she reached for a rag and wiped her palms. &quot;I hope you enjoyed the festival last night.  Hmm..if you enjoyed it a bit too much I have something to help.&quot; Motions over to a steaming pot to her right. &quot;Or perhaps I could interest you in a morning meal?&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uqueenhera.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Queen Hera</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 206<br> <font color=#993300>(8/30/02 6:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=387.topic&index=10>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.themiscrya.i-p.com/qhera.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Curiosity Killed the Cat</span><hr size=1> Curiosity got the best of the Queen of the Gods, that day.  Watching her white peacock in the gardens, something called her to the reflecting pool.  Without sound, she moved towards the pool.   The long shimmery dress barely gave any hint that the Goddess was even walking.  Cold frigid blue eyes set upon the pool, not leaving it's surface as she slowely neared it.  And then she stopped.  Looking down into the reflection, the Queen's right brow slowely crooked upward in a sharp slant.  A long arm and slender dark sleeved arm reached out to dance pale digits across the refection causing a small ripple.  <br>
<br>
The front door and windows of the Labrys suddenly burst open with a chilled breeze behind them that moved about the room touching the occupants.  As quickly as it moved in, the windows and door closed to silence. <p>~~<<<<<<{{{{@</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=cyrene>Cyrene</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#993300>(8/30/02 7:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=387.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/cyreneamphipolis/cyrene005.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Curiosity Killed the Cat</span><hr size=1> The sudden outburst caused Cyrene's knuckles to turn white as she gripped the counter to keep from jumping.  Gasping for air as the chill touched her skin, she trembled and held on.<br>
Then it was gone.<br>
Pale eyes narrowed as she glared at the doors and windows, confused she grasped her upper arms in an attempt to warm them.<br>
&quot;I'm new here, does that happen often?&quot; There was a familiar sent carried with the wind, something she could just about put her finger on before it skittered away into her consciousness.<br>
&quot;Something to do with the sea air hitting the mountain air?&quot; Cyrene cast a questioning look at Varia. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uqueenvaria.showPublicProfile?language=EN>QueenVaria</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://hometown.aol.com/variaavande/images/tsianina2.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 658<br> <font color=#993300>(8/31/02 4:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=387.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://hometown.aol.com/cristalc15/images/varia3sm.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Curiosity Killed the Cat</span><hr size=1> Varia did jump at that breeze, and she squeaked too. Then shaking her head to Cyrene's questions she eyed the windows warily. "Bet it was one of the gods... they like to sneak around like that." She eyed once more and then double checked the locks, finding them secure. "Yep, it was one of the gods." <p><html> <center> <font face="vivaldi" size="+2" color="#ff0000"> ~Varia Angelina Avande~ </font> </html></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=cyrene>Cyrene</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#993300>(8/31/02 9:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=387.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/cyreneamphipolis/cyrene005.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Curiosity Killed the Cat</span><hr size=1> Cyrene didn't know whether she could be confused, hurt, or angry, so she was all three at once.  She'd watched Varia move around the room, and even before she spoke those words, she had a suspicion.  Though she had no idea which god would...eh.<br>
<br>
Pushing the thoughts from her mind she shrugged and laughed.  &quot;Well, next time they'll have to leave their name.  I'll leave an offering for them in thanks for helping me dust the tavern.&quot; Offering a salute to the air, the older woman smiled at Varia and moved over to the pot of stew to give it a stir.<br>
