<br>
Shifting a quick glance to Varia, she gathered two bowls and filled them with the famous brew.  Rabbit stew spiced with onions and curry, thick root vegetables and small bits of hard dried bread. A favorite dish people were known to make a day's detour from their travels to stop at her tavern.<br>
<br>
Without thought she placed the dish in front of Varia, and the empty space beside her near the Queen of the Gods.  Turning back 'round she poured tankards of water, those as well were placed next to the bowls.  A plate of bread and sweet hard cheese between the two bowls.<br>
<br>
Turning her attention once more to the Queen of the gods, pale azure defensive, apprehensive, yet showing no disrespect.<br>
<br>
&quot;Thank you,&quot; the older woman spoke softly as she accepted the dinars from Varia never allowing her eyes to leave the Olympian's.  After a moment, she found her heart catch in her throat on it's way up to escape the confines of her chest.  She had to break contact from the unearthly gaze and found solace in wiping a quite clean spot on the counter. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uqueenhera.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Queen Hera</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 211<br> <font color=#993300>(8/31/02 11:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=387.topic&index=17>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.themiscrya.i-p.com/lilhera.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The sound of silence.</span><hr size=1> Slowely she turned her eyes to Varia and gave her a greeting, "Hello, Varia."  Then her head tilted towards the tavern keeper who seemed determined to finish her tasks despite the Goddesses appearance.  Hera could sense and see Cyrene's nervousness.  A hard to come by smile attempted to rise her lips, but they moved only ever slightly.<br>
<br>
"I was told that you needed to speak to me," Her voice was cold, despite the genuine attempt at being nice.  Hera's eyes not leaving Cyrene.<br>
