<br>
Even though she was nervous, she got straight to the point. &quot;Y..yes, you see.  I have a simple question for a not so simple issue. Something has come to my attention.  The herb Silphium, it, sometimes stops children from being conceived. In Greece, the guard has started to attack herb retails and hedgwitches alike who have been rumored to sell, or use it.&quot;<br>
<br>
Putting the bar towel down she moved out from behind the bar, wiping her palms on her apron.  Drawing closer, she once again met the Goddesses' eyes.<br>
<br>
&quot;I have a way to distribute it by way of Egypt's Northern Coast, and a network of vendors, I've done business for in my years as a tavern owner, who are willing to help. All this and I thought of perhaps hiring guards for the shipments, and asking for volunteer help, here, to make sure it is safely given to those in need.&quot; With this her brows furrowed, thoughts could be seen working behind pale azure.<br>
<br>
&quot;The point to this is.  I belive it should be a woman's right to chose, if she can, whether or not to have children. Yet I am simply a mortal woman.  In your infinite wisdom, do you feel it is right for a woman to chose and to be given the opportunity?&quot; The older woman grew silent, her gaze lingering for a moment, before she bowed her head in humble respect, and awaited Hera's reply. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uqueenhera.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Queen Hera</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 212<br> <font color=#993300>(9/1/02 11:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=387.topic&index=19>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.themiscrya.i-p.com/lilhera.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The sound of silence.</span><hr size=1> The idea that women did not want to bear children was odd to the Goddess of Childbirth.  But it was not foreign.  In moments when she attended a mortal birth, she found that there were mothers who cursed the birth of their child.  When this happened, Hera often left quickly.  <br>
<br>
For a moment, she gazed into Cyrene's eyes.  Almost as if she was reading her from the inside.  "I understand what you are saying.  I do believe that to bear a child is the most wonderful thing in a woman's life.  But, perhaps some women should not find the time right...or even desire this gift.  If a woman is of this manner.  Then perhaps the woman should make the final decision.  I would rather that...then she rip the life from her womb."  Her eyes flashed to the eyelet of a peafowls feather as she said the word. <p>~~<<<<<<{{{{@</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=cyrene>Cyrene</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#993300>(9/1/02 11:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=387.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/cyreneamphipolis/cyrene005.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The sound of silence.</span><hr size=1> Glancing away from the goddess in respect, she knotted her hands together. &quot;Thank you for your honesty.  I didn't wish to offend the goddess of birth, the task I have chosen to undertake is going to be difficult enough without a goddess' rage.&quot;<br>
